00346     // Transforms strings in IDs: zero IDs are progressively assigned

00350     // The ID values are organizad in the same parsing order.
00351 
00352     switch (parsing) {
00353     case SPO:
00354         if (qstring.x[0] != '?') {
00355             qid.q.x = dictionary->retrieveID(qstring.x, VOC_SUBJECT);
00356 
00357             if (qstring.y[0] != '?') {
00358                 qid.q.y = dictionary->retrieveID(qstring.y, VOC_PREDICATE);

00360                 qid.q.y = 0;

00370                 qid.q.z = 0;

00508 bool BitmapTriples::ask(string q) {
00509     bool checkf = false;
00510     Query query = parseQ(q);
00511 
00512     if (query.q.x == ERROR) {
00513         cout << "  - First element was not found in the dictionary:" << endl;
00514     }
00515     if (query.q.y == ERROR) {
00516         cout << "  - Second element was not found in the dictionary:" << endl;
00517     }
00518     if (query.q.z == ERROR) {
00519         cout << "  - Third element was not found in the dictionary:" << endl;
00520     }
00521     if ((query.q.x == ERROR) || (query.q.y == ERROR) || (query.q.z == ERROR)) {
00522         return false;
00523     }
00524 
00525     if (query.variables != ERROR) {
00526         unsigned int beginY = bitmapY->select1(query.q.x);
00527         unsigned int endY = bitmapY->select1(query.q.x + 1);
00528         unsigned int sizeY = endY - beginY - 1;
00529 
00530         if (sizeY > 0) {
00531             if (query.variables == 2) {
00532                 // In this point we guarantee that exist at least one triple
00533                 // (X, ?y, ?z) -> return true
00534                 checkf = true;
00535             } else {
00536                 fseek(fileY, (beginY - query.q.x + 1) * INT32, SEEK_SET);
00537                 unsigned int *bufferY = new unsigned int[sizeY];
00538                 size_t s = fread(bufferY, INT32, sizeY, fileY);
00539                 unsigned int *ptr = lower_bound(bufferY, bufferY + sizeY,
00540                         query.q.y);
00541 
00542                 if ((ptr != NULL) && (*ptr == query.q.y)) {
00543                     if (query.variables == 1) {
00544                         // In this point we guarantee that exist at least one 
00545                         // triple (X, Y, ?z) -> return true
00546                         checkf = true;
00547                     } else {
00548                         unsigned int pY = bitmapY->rank0(beginY) + (ptr
00549                                 - bufferY) + 1;
00550                         unsigned int beginZ = bitmapZ->select1(pY) - pY + 1;
00551                         unsigned int endZ = bitmapZ->select1(pY + 1) - pY;
00552                         unsigned int sizeZ = endZ - beginZ;
00553 
00554                         fseek(fileZ, beginZ * INT32, SEEK_SET);
00555                         unsigned int *bufferZ = new unsigned int[sizeZ];
00556                         s = fread(bufferZ, INT32, sizeZ, fileZ);
00557                         ptr = lower_bound(bufferZ, bufferZ + sizeZ, query.q.z);
00558 
00559                         if ((ptr != NULL) && (*ptr == query.q.z)) {
00560                             // The triple (X, Y, Z) exists in the dataset
00561                             checkf = true;
00562                         }
00563 
00564                         delete[] bufferZ;
00565                     }
00566                 }
00567 
00568                 delete[] bufferY;
00569             }
00570         }
00571     } else {
00572         cout
00573                 << "   <WARNING> This query is not currently supported: we are currently working!"
00574                 << endl;
00575     }
00576 
00577     return checkf;
00578 }

00603 int BitmapTriples::select(string q, vector<TripleString> **triples) {
00604     uint results = 0;
00605     Query query = parseQ(q);
00606 
00607     if (query.q.x == ERROR) {

00612     }
00613     if (query.q.z == ERROR) {
00614         cout << "  - Third element was not found in the dictionary:" << endl;
00615     }

00626

00628             fseek(fileY, (beginY - query.q.x + 1) * INT32, SEEK_SET);

00630             size_t s = fread(bufferY, INT32, sizeY, fileY);
00631 
00632             unsigned int pY, beginZ, endZ;
00633             int sizeZ;

00636                 // Retrieving the coordinate Y

00638                         query.q.y);

00641                     pY = bitmapY->rank0(beginY) + (ptr - bufferY) + 1;
00642                     beginZ = bitmapZ->select1(pY) - pY + 1;
00643                     endZ = bitmapZ->select1(pY + 1) - pY;
00644                     sizeZ = endZ - beginZ;
00645 
00646                     bufferY[0] = *ptr;

00650                 }

00655                 endZ = bitmapZ->select1(pY + sizeY) - (pY + sizeY - 1);
00656                 sizeZ = endZ - beginZ;

00664             // Building a result table

00667 
00668             string subject, object, predicate;
00669             uint i = 0, readZ = 0;
00670 
00671             if (parsing <= SOP)

00680                 if ((parsing == PSO) || (parsing == OSP))

00683                 else if ((parsing == SPO) || (parsing == OPS))

00685                             VOC_PREDICATE);
00686                 else
00687                     object = dictionary->retrieveString(bufferY[y - 1],
00688                             VOC_OBJECT);

00691                 sizeZ = endZ - beginZ;

00694                     if ((parsing == POS) || (parsing == OPS))
00695                         subject = dictionary->retrieveString(bufferZ[readZ],
00696                                 VOC_SUBJECT);

00699                                 VOC_PREDICATE);
00700                     else
00701                         object = dictionary->retrieveString(bufferZ[readZ],
00702                                 VOC_OBJECT);

00706                     (*vresult)[readZ].z = object;

00709                 }

01148 int BitmapTriples::getLength(vector<minipair> * triplesSub, int current,
01149         MiniHashTable *subLengths) {
01150 
01151     //cout<<"Entering getlength for:"<<current<<endl;
01152     //fflush(stdout);
01153     unsigned int first = 0;
01154     unsigned int next = 0;
01155     string firstString = "", nextString = "";
01156     int pos = FindTransition(*triplesSub, current); //binary search
01157     int maxlength = 0, length = 0;
01158     MINIHASHREC *recordRetrieve;
01159     if (pos < 0)
01160         return 0; //no transition
01161     while (pos < triplesSub->size()) {
01162         first = triplesSub->at(pos).source;
01163         if (first != current)
01164             break;
01165         next = triplesSub->at(pos).target;
01166         //cout<<"next:"<<next<<endl;
01167         //fflush(stdout);
01168         sprintf((char*) firstString.c_str(), "%d", first);
01169         sprintf((char*) nextString.c_str(), "%d", next);
01170         recordRetrieve = subLengths->hashsearch((char*) nextString.c_str());
01171         if (recordRetrieve != NULL) {
01172             length = recordRetrieve->id;
01173         } else {
01174             length = getLength(triplesSub, next, subLengths) + 1;
01175         }
01176         if (length > maxlength) {
01177             subLengths->hashinsert((char*) firstString.c_str(), length);
01178             maxlength = length;
01179         }
01180         pos++;
01181     }
01182     return maxlength;
01183 }

01190 unsigned int BitmapTriples::write(vector<TripleID> &graph, string path) {
01191     string output = path;
01192     FILE *fileY = fopen((output.append(".hdt.triples.Y")).c_str(), "w+");
01193 
01194     output = path;
01195     FILE *fileZ = fopen((output.append(".hdt.triples.Z")).c_str(), "w+");
01196 
01197     unsigned int repeated = 0;
01198     unsigned int x = graph[0].x, y = graph[0].y, z = 0;
01199 
01200     unsigned int ys = 1, zs = 0;
01201     unsigned int tys = 0, tzs = 0;
01202     vector<unsigned int> v_ys, v_zs;
01203 
01204     fwrite(&y, INT32, 1, fileY);
01205 
01206     for (unsigned int i = 0; i < graph.size(); i++) {
01207         if (x == graph[i].x) {
01208             if (y == graph[i].y) {
01209                 if (z != graph[i].z) {
01210                     z = graph[i].z;
01211 
01212                     fwrite(&z, INT32, 1, fileZ);
01213                     zs++;
01214                 } else {
01215                     repeated++;
01216                 }
01217             } else {
01218                 // Change of Y coordinate
01219                 y = graph[i].y;
01220                 z = graph[i].z;
01221 
01222                 fwrite(&y, INT32, 1, fileY);
01223                 fwrite(&z, INT32, 1, fileZ);
01224 
01225                 ys++;
01226                 v_zs.push_back(zs);
01227                 tzs += zs;
01228                 zs = 1;
01229             }
01230         } else {
01231             // Change of X and Y coordinates
01232             x = graph[i].x;
01233             y = graph[i].y;
01234             z = graph[i].z;
01235 
01236             fwrite(&y, INT32, 1, fileY);
01237             fwrite(&z, INT32, 1, fileZ);
01238 
01239             v_ys.push_back(ys);
01240             tys += ys;
01241             ys = 1;
01242             v_zs.push_back(zs);
01243             tzs += zs;
01244             zs = 1;
01245         }
01246     }
01247 
01248     v_ys.push_back(ys);
01249     tys += ys;
01250     v_zs.push_back(zs);
01251     tzs += zs;
01252 
01253     fclose(fileY);
01254     fclose(fileZ);
01255 
01256     BitString *bsy = new BitString(tys + v_ys.size() + 1);
01257     buildBitString(&bsy, &v_ys, v_ys.size());
01258 
01259     BitString *bsz = new BitString(tzs + v_zs.size() + 1);
01260     buildBitString(&bsz, &v_zs, v_zs.size());
01261 
01262     // Building bitsequences
01263     BitSequence *bitmapY = new BitSequenceRG(*bsy, 20);
01264     BitSequence *bitmapZ = new BitSequenceRG(*bsz, 20);
01265 
01266     delete bsy;
01267     delete bsz;
01268 
01269     output = path;
01270     output.append(".hdt.triples.BY");
01271     ofstream fp1(output.c_str());
01272 
01273     output = path;
01274     output.append(".hdt.triples.BZ");
01275     ofstream fp2(output.c_str());
01276 
01277     if (fp1.good()) {
01278         bitmapY->save(fp1);
01279         fp1.close();
01280     }
01281 
01282     if (fp2.good()) {
01283         bitmapZ->save(fp2);
01284         fp2.close();
01285     }
01286 
01287     return graph.size() - repeated;
01288 }

01304 void BitmapTriples::buildBitString(BitString **bs, vector<uint> *v, uint elems) {
01305     (*bs)->setBit(0, true);
01306     uint pos = 0;
01307 
01308     for (uint i = 0; i < elems; i++) {
01309         (*bs)->setBit((*v)[i] + pos + 1, true);
01310         pos += (*v)[i] + 1;
01311     }
